install git for windows
http://msysgit.github.io/

set basic configuration
http://git-scm.com/book/en/Getting-Started-First-Time-Git-Setup
$ git config --global user.name "John Doe"
$ git config --global user.email johndoe@example.com

check the configuration set
git config --list


authentication to git with clonning a remote repository
https://github.com/mlk0/tProj.git
git clone https://github.com/mlk0/tProj.git


adding a new file
git add -A

commiting
git commit -m 'the comment'

pushing the changes
git push origin branchName

getting the changes
git pull origin branchName

merging 2 banches
git merge theOtherBranch
	- the command is issued out of the destination branch and in it will be merged theOtherBranch

rebasing 2 branchs
git rebase origin master
	- the current branch is rebased with the content that is coming from master


initialize a new repo in a folder where he project is stored
git init

create a remote repository for the locally created repository
git remote add origin https://github.com/mlk0/MyAwesomePreciousConsoleApp.git
git remote add origin https://github.com/mlk0/MyAwesomeConsole.git
git remote add origin http://me@myrepo/my/repo.git
git remote add origin  https://github.com/mlk0/MyMVC.git
git remote add origin  https://github.com/mlk0/MyMvc.git


configure git to ignore bin or other files - nuget packages
when navigated to the folder, issue the command
touch .gitignore
that will create an empty file
Than, paste the official content for the .gitignore file for c# projects from 
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/2143956/gitignore-for-visual-studio-projects-and-solutions

# Revert changes to modified files.
git reset --hard

# Remove all untracked files and directories.
git clean -fd


# remove local repository
rm -rf .git
	deletes the .git folder

git push -u origin master




